132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST SPECIAL SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1862
S.P. 732 In Senate, May 5, 2025
An Act to Provide That Authority over In-person Sports Betting
Resides Solely with the Gambling Control Board
Received by the Secretary of the Senate on May 1, 2025. Referred to the Committee on
Veterans and Legal Affairs pursuant to Joint Rule 308.2 and ordered printed.
DAREK M. GRANT
Secretary of the Senate
Presented by Senator BALDACCI of Penobscot.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 8 MRSA §1220 is enacted to read:
3 §1220. Jurisdiction
4 Notwithstanding any provision of law to the contrary, jurisdiction over sports wagering
5 conducted in person on the property of a facility operator is vested solely in the Gambling
6 Control Board established in section 1002.
7 SUMMARY
88 This bill provides that jurisdiction over sports wagering conducted in person on the
99 property of a facility operator is vested solely in the Department of Public Safety, Gambling
1100 Control Board.
